### `api/server.js`
Complete Express server with:
- MongoDB connection via MONGODB_URI env var (default: mongodb://localhost:27017/tchopetyamo)
- CORS enabled
- Routes: /api/menu, /api/orders, /api/customers
- Error handling middleware
- Listen on PORT env var (default 3001)

### `api/models/MenuItem.js`
Mongoose schema:
- name: String required
- category: String enum ['BEIGNETS','SALADES','BOISSON','POULETS','BURGER','MENUS_COMPOSES'] required
- price: Number required
- description: String
- available: Boolean default true
- timestamps: true

### `api/models/Order.js`
Mongoose schema:
- customerName: String required
- customerPhone: String
- deliveryAddress: String
- items: array of { menuItemId: ObjectId ref MenuItem, name: String, price: Number, quantity: Number }
- totalAmount: Number required
- status: String enum ['pending','confirmed','preparing','ready','delivered','cancelled'] default 'pending'
- notes: String
- timestamps: true

### `api/routes/menu.js`
- GET / - list all menu items (support ?category= filter, ?available=true)
- GET /:id - get one
- POST / - create
- PUT /:id - update
- DELETE /:id - delete

### `api/routes/orders.js`
- GET / - list all orders (support ?status= filter)
- GET /:id - get one order (populate menu items)
- POST / - create order (validate items, calculate total, embed name+price snapshot)
- PUT /:id - update order (status, notes, deliveryAddress - cannot update if cancelled/delivered)
- DELETE /:id - cancel order (set status to 'cancelled')

### `api/seed.js`
Seeds all the menu items from the data above into MongoDB. Connect to DB, clear MenuItem collection, insert all items, then disconnect.

