### `mcp-server/index.js`
MCP server using stdio transport. Exposes these tools that call the CRUD API at API_URL (default http://localhost:3001):

1. `get_menu` - Get menu items. Input: { category?: string, available?: boolean }
2. `get_menu_item` - Get a single menu item by ID. Input: { id: string }
3. `create_order` - Place a new order. Input: { customerName: string, customerPhone?: string, deliveryAddress?: string, items: Array<{menuItemId: string, quantity: number}>, notes?: string }
4. `get_order` - Get order details by ID. Input: { orderId: string }
5. `update_order` - Update order status or details. Input: { orderId: string, status?: string, notes?: string, deliveryAddress?: string }
6. `cancel_order` - Cancel an order. Input: { orderId: string }
7. `list_orders` - List orders with optional filter. Input: { customerPhone?: string, status?: string }

Use `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/index.js` Server class and `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/stdio.js` StdioServerTransport.
Use node-fetch for HTTP calls.

